Eastern Cape Premier Oscar Mabuyane says the Cuban doctors have come at a crucial time for the province. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Eastern Cape government has welcomed Cuban doctors to East London. The group of 20 includes physicians, specialists and biostatisticians, among others. The doctors will be helping the province in the fight against COVID-19. Premier Oscar Mabuyane says the Cuban doctors have come at a crucial time for the province. READ: Outcry in Algeria after pregnant doctor dies of COVID-19 The Eastern Cape has more than 1,800 coronavirus infections and there have been 32 deaths. Mabuyane says South African doctors, who are unemployed or just out of university, should come forward and report for duty. The premier has also voiced his displeasure at US Secretary of State, Mike Pompeo's recent criticism of South Africa allowing Cuba to send help. Mabuyane has stressed that Cuba's assistance is greatly appreciated. The Cuban doctors say they're ready to roll up their sleeves and join forces with their South African counterparts. READ: Cuban doctors report to work on Monday The doctors will be assigned throughout the Eastern Cape to work with local doctors already in the field. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.